# Architecture

- Follow the existing project structure.
- Keep components focused on a single responsibility.
- Separate UI, business logic, and data access.
- Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Avoid deeply nested components and large utility files.

# React / Next.js

- Prefer Server Components when possible.
- Use Client Components only when browser APIs or React hooks require them.
- Minimize `useEffect`. Avoid unnecessary state.
- Prefer derived state over duplicated state.
- Lazy-load heavy components. Dynamically import large libraries.
- Optimize images with Next.js `Image`.
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders.
